theorem interior_closure_interior_closure_subset_closure
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    interior (closure (interior (closure A))) ⊆ closure A := by
  open Set in
  -- First, use `interior_subset` to go from the interior to the surrounding closure.
  have h₁ :
      interior (closure (interior (closure A))) ⊆
        closure (interior (closure A)) :=
    interior_subset
  -- Next, use monotonicity of `closure` to relate to `closure A`.
  have h₂ :
      closure (interior (closure A)) ⊆ closure A := by
    have h_int : interior (closure A) ⊆ closure A := interior_subset
    exact closure_mono h_int
  -- Combine the two inclusions.
  exact h₁.trans h₂

theorem closure_interior_closure_subset_closure {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A : Set X} :
    closure (interior (closure A)) ⊆ closure A := by
  have h : interior (closure A) ⊆ closure A := interior_subset
  exact closure_mono h

theorem interior_closure_subset_closure_interior_closure {X : Type*}
    [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    interior (closure A) ⊆ closure (interior (closure A)) := by
  intro x hx
  exact subset_closure hx
